---
import BaseLayout        from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header            from '../components/astro/Header.astro';
import Footer            from '../components/astro/Footer.astro';
import Accordion         from '../components/astro/Accordion.astro';
import SurvivalRateChart from '../components/vue/SurvivalRateChart.vue';
import { Breadcrumbs }   from "astro-breadcrumbs";

import "astro-breadcrumbs/breadcrumbs.css";
---

<BaseLayout title="Prostate Hub - Stage 1">
  <Header />
  
  <main class="my-8 container mx-auto px-4">
    <section class="text-center p-8 mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Stage 1: Early Stage Prostate Cancer</h1>
      <p class="text-lg max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        Information about Stage 1 prostate cancer, treatment options, and resources for newly diagnosed patients.
      </p>
    </section>
    <div class="mb-2">
      <Breadcrumbs separatorAriaHidden={false} linkTextFormat="capitalized">
        <svg
          slot="separator"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          width="24"
          height="24"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2"
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          ><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline>
        </svg>
      </Breadcrumbs>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-8">
      <div class="md:w-1/3 p-4">
        <div class="space-y-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-2xl font-serif">Stage 1 prostate cancer has a very high 5-year survival rate of over 99%.</p>
          <div class="mt-15 mb-6">
             <SurvivalRateChart client:load stage="1" survivalRate={99} />
          </div>
          <p class="text-2xl font-serif">Approximately 19% of men diagnosed with prostate cancer fall into the low-risk group, which includes Stage 1.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="md:w-2/3">
          <Accordion title="What is Stage 1 Prostate Cancer?" initiallyOpen={true}>
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <p>Stage 1 prostate cancer means the cancer is small and contained entirely within the prostate. At this stage:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>The cancer cannot be felt during a digital rectal exam</li>
                <li>The cancer is microscopic and only found through a biopsy</li>
                <li>PSA levels are usually below 10 ng/mL</li>
                <li>The Gleason score is typically 6 or lower</li>
              </ul>
              <p>Stage 1 prostate cancer has an excellent prognosis, with many treatment options available.</p>
            </div>
          </Accordion>
          
          <Accordion title="Treatment Options">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg">Active Surveillance</h3>
              <p>For many Stage 1 patients, doctors recommend active surveillance rather than immediate treatment. This involves:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>Regular PSA tests (every 3-6 months)</li>
                <li>Digital rectal exams (every 6-12 months)</li>
                <li>Repeat biopsies (usually every 1-3 years)</li>
              </ul>
              
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6">Radical Prostatectomy</h3>
              <p>Surgical removal of the entire prostate gland and some surrounding tissue.</p>
              
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mt-6">Radiation Therapy</h3>
              <p>Uses high-energy rays to kill cancer cells. Two main types:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>External beam radiation therapy (EBRT)</li>
                <li>Brachytherapy (internal radiation)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </Accordion>
          
          <Accordion title="Support Options">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <p>Connecting with support groups and resources can help you navigate your diagnosis:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Prostate Cancer Support Groups in New Zealand</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Online Forums for Newly Diagnosed Patients</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Financial Assistance Resources</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </Accordion>
          
          <Accordion title="New Zealand Medical Resources">
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <p>Reliable New Zealand-specific resources for Stage 1 prostate cancer:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">New Zealand Guidelines for Management of Prostate Cancer</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Cancer Society of New Zealand</a></li>
                <li><a href="#" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Ministry of Health Treatment Information</a></li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </Accordion>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>